3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,160
This is CEO Theo of Re:Try. Did you get home safely?

4
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:26,880
Let's work on this project together, Artist Lee.

5
00:00:27,860 --> 00:00:29,820
I'm sorry.

6
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:37,070
How can this be?

7
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,600
Why are you...

8
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:46,110
The first time I ran away from you...

9
00:00:46,110 --> 00:00:51,300
[Year 2015, Us on Graduation Day]

10
00:00:53,780 --> 00:00:56,380
Hey! I thought you weren't coming.

11
00:00:56,380 --> 00:00:58,820
- What took you so long?
- Sorry.

12
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:00,750
Something came up.

13
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:03,140
I'm sure you had something come up.

14
00:01:03,140 --> 00:01:05,800
- Hey! You brought it.
- What?

15
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,200
Oh, yes.

16
00:01:09,190 --> 00:01:11,890
Should we take a picture with this?

17
00:01:11,890 --> 00:01:13,450
Hey, take a picture for me.

18
00:01:13,450 --> 00:01:17,200
Gosh, you know I'm great at taking pictures.

19
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,530
- Hey, hurry and take it. It's cold.
- Okay.

20
00:01:19,530 --> 00:01:21,650
I guess you can...

21
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:23,900
hold the bouquet.

22
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,440
All right. Look that way again.

23
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:28,680
- Please look this way! Here it goes.
- And smile a little!

24
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:32,030
One, two, three!

25
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:38,130
Congrats on your graduation.

26
00:01:38,130 --> 00:01:40,320
I look forward to the future.

27
00:01:49,290 --> 00:01:51,460
The camera sure is nice.

28
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:55,990
Let's go.

29
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,480
Wh-Where to?

30
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:01,670
What's this? Don't you remember we agreed to drink with them today?

31
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,380
- Hurry and come!
- He said he's hungry.

32
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:06,000
- Okay, we're coming.
- He said I'm hungry.

33
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,210
- Let's go.
- Wait!

34
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:09,620
What?

35
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,890
I have something to tell you.

36
00:02:12,890 --> 00:02:15,480
What is it? Tell me on the way. Aren't you hungry?

37
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:18,010
It's something I want only you to hear.

38
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,170
Gosh, what could it be?

39
00:02:21,170 --> 00:02:23,150
I'm a little worried.

40
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,210
Wait a second.

41
00:02:25,210 --> 00:02:27,820
- Hey, you guys, go ahead.
- Why? What is it? Tell me.

42
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:30,970
Gosh, we'll be right there. Just go on ahead.

43
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:35,490
It's fine now, right?

44
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:37,450
What is it? Tell me.

45
00:02:43,790 --> 00:02:46,740
- What's the matter—
- I like you.

46
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:55,480
- I like you, too.
- No...

47
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,710
What I meant was...

48
00:03:00,730 --> 00:03:03,270
The way I like you...

49
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:08,170
is in this way.

50
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:15,560
Hey.

51
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,800
You... Wait...

52
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:24,530
- Hold on.
- Well, sorry.

53
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:27,640
I'll be off.

54
00:03:30,450 --> 00:03:32,420
Hey, Wan...

55
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:35,480
Hey, Lee Wan!

56
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:46,930
Hey, Lee Wan!

57
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:49,800
Hey, Wan!

58
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:54,030
Lee Wan?

59
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:56,930
Hey, where are you guys? What's taking so long?

60
00:03:56,930 --> 00:03:59,020
Do you know Wan's home telephone number?

61
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:01,050
Or his sister's phone number?

62
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:02,890
Did he run off again?

63
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,800
Stop saying useless things. Do you know the number?

64
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,610
Who would know if you don't?

65
00:04:06,610 --> 00:04:08,820
Just hurry and come here.

66
00:04:10,540 --> 00:04:12,780
Where the heck did he go?

67
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:29,040
On that day,

68
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,340
I abandoned everything and ran away,

69
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:34,960
deciding to hide forever.

70
00:04:38,830 --> 00:04:43,980
[August 8, 2015, When We Were Twenty Years Old]

71
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:49,170
Thank you.

72
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,640
Hey! Aunt's back is going to break.

73
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:55,290
Why don't you come out and help?

74
00:05:00,540 --> 00:05:04,190
♪ Happy birthday to you! ♪

75
00:05:04,190 --> 00:05:06,590
♪ Happy birthday, dear Shin Gi Tae ♪

76
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:09,630
♪ Happy birthday to you! ♪

77
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:13,150
Birthday shot! Birthday shot!

78
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:16,120
- Table four.
- Birthday shot! Birthday shot!

79
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:32,160
Thank you.

80
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:38,950
I hated myself because I kept expecting you to come

81
00:05:38,950 --> 00:05:40,890
when there was no way you would.

82
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:43,470
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

83
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:47,960
Beautiful Lady, please ask the next question.

84
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,190
It's my turn now.

85
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:54,090
"I have a crush on one of the people here."

86
00:05:54,090 --> 00:05:55,700
I do. On three people.

87
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,460
- I also have one!
- On one person.

88
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:01,180
Gosh, Gi Tae's crush must not be here.

89
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:04,250
Hey, why the heck do you still have all those fingers?

90
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:10,280
In that case! "I actually have a secret lover."

91
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:13,680
Hey, what kind of question is that?

92
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,340
Hey, you have one, haven't you?

93
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:18,550
I also have... Wait, I don't.

94
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:21,560
Even our Jin Seok also has a lover.

95
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,320
You two can take a shot then.

96
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,360
Shall we take a shot?

97
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:29,000
- Come on, let's all just take a shot!
- Okay, okay!

98
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,640
Cheers!

99
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:53,900
[Wan]

100
00:06:58,910 --> 00:07:03,630
[Wan]

101
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,570
The number you dialed does not exist.

102
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:12,290
Please check and dial again.

103
00:07:12,290 --> 00:07:13,730
It was weird.

104
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:17,780
He was the one who liked me, and I was the one who pushed him away,

105
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:19,930
but then he disappeared,

106
00:07:19,930 --> 00:07:23,180
and I was the one left behind.

107
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:27,570
We chose computers over dating.
[Year 2019, When We Were Twenty-four Years Old]

108
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:30,780
Today, we finally succeeded in getting our start-up investments!

109
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:32,420
Yes!

110
00:07:33,650 --> 00:07:36,830
- Hey.
- Let's go!

111
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:40,290
- Hey! I was in school for ten years, all right?
- Even when I was unbelievably happy...

112
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:42,960
Where did my youth and love go?
[Wan]

113
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,370
Anyhow, we're seeing the fruits of our labor today. All right?

114
00:07:45,370 --> 00:07:47,970
- Wait. Wait a moment!
- Why?
- Today...

115
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:49,840
- Wan...
- Let's drink until we drop!

116
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,530
Okay. No one stop me this time, okay? I'm going to let loose.

117
00:07:52,530 --> 00:07:55,700
- All right.
- Cheers, cheers.

118
00:07:56,350 --> 00:08:01,880
[Gi Tae]
[My aunt passed...]

119
00:08:05,260 --> 00:08:10,010
Even when I was unbelievably sad...

120
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,830
Are you really not going to call anyone over?

121
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:19,100
My aunt passed away.
[Gi Tae]

122
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:28,640
I couldn't bring myself to contact you.

123
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:34,440
- Yes, yes.
- A bottle of water, please.

124
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:37,000
- One bottle of water? Okay.
- Boss, one fried chicken, please.

125
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,830
One more fried chicken? Okay.

126
00:08:38,830 --> 00:08:40,980
One more fried chicken, please!

127
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:42,790
Are four shot glasses enough?

128
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:45,460
Coming right out!

129
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:47,320
[When you miss someone so much but can't see them, just draw the good times you had together. That's enough.]

130
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:51,880
I began to draw every time you crossed my mind
[When you miss someone so much but can't see them, just draw the good times you had together. That's enough.]

131
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:55,720
and drawing soon became my everything.

132
00:08:56,500 --> 00:09:02,190
And astoundingly, people started to react to my drawings.

133
00:09:02,190 --> 00:09:04,880
The drawing is very nice.

134
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:09,040
I'm at ease whenever I see these drawings.

135
00:09:12,330 --> 00:09:15,400
I'm Producer Ahn from Magic Toon.

136
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,950
Author Lee Wan, you're qualified

137
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:21,190
for the final interview of the new artist boot camp.

138
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:23,630
Now I also

139
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:27,370
have the chance to forget you and enter a different world.

140
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:31,610
[Ian's Record]

141
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:35,410
The final interview is at 1 p.m.

142
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:39,400
I'll meet you at Magic Toon Business Center.
[Magic Toon Business Center]

143
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,420
- Mr. Wan?
- Hello.

144
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:43,820
Have a seat.

145
00:09:45,610 --> 00:09:48,160
The competition was very fierce this time.

146
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:51,300
And it was the best condition for a new artist to debut.

147
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:56,530
Many applied for the merit of working abroad and gaining various experiences.

148
00:09:56,530 --> 00:10:00,200
Yes, thank you for giving me this opportunity.

149
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,990
And Mr. Wan,

150
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:06,190
we contacted you first after viewing your blog.

151
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:08,750
Your first and second-round submissions were very good.

152
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:11,500
Therefore, we really wanted to have you join us.

153
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,800
I see.

154
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:17,760
If you join the camp, you'll be abroad for at least one year. Are you okay with that?

155
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:20,380
Yes. I'm okay with that.

156
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:22,360
Are you sure?

157
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:28,210
When drawing, what do you start with?

158
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,660
Well, usually...

159
00:10:30,660 --> 00:10:33,280
I start with the face.

160
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:34,990
The face?

161
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:38,490
This face...

162
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:43,030
Did you know there's only one face in your webtoons?

163
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,350
All the characters have the same face.

164
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:49,450
The same expressions and the same dialogue.

165
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:55,700
Are you unable... to abandon this character?

166
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:04,160
Mr. Wan, our camp needs an artist

167
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:08,330
who can draw various pictures with a wide spectrum.

168
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:12,640
An artist who's buried in one story and one emotion...

169
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:16,510
can only draw one face.

170
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:21,490
It will be difficult for you to join us for this camp,

171
00:11:21,490 --> 00:11:24,120
but I hope to see you again soon.

172
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,580
Well, then...

173
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,950
Producer Ahn!

174
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:35,630
I still thank you.

175
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:38,060
I gained a lot of courage thanks to your comments on my blog

176
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:40,650
for the past few years.

177
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:42,920
Comments?

178
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,930
Gameboy.

179
00:11:44,930 --> 00:11:47,780
Gameboy?

180
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:52,810
Aren't you the one who's been posting comments on my blog?

181
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:56,220
The nickname was Gameboy.

182
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:00,580
It wasn't me. I'll get going.

183
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:11,610
Then who is Gameboy?

184
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:17,480
Hey, Nuna. I'm on my way to Daejeon.

185
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,560
Who...

186
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:27,380
Hello. I'm Theo, CEO of the gaming company, Re:Try.

187
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:30,760
I'd like to meet you to discuss a character creation job.

188
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:33,450
I'm contacting you through your blog, "Cartoon Diaries."

189
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:36,760
How do you feel about meeting at 11 a.m. tomorrow?

190
00:12:38,930 --> 00:12:42,440
An opportunity that seemed to have dropped from the sky.

191
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:46,780
I stood at the crossroads of choices once again.

192
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:51,550
This is CEO Theo of Re:Try. Did you get home safely?

193
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:55,370
Let's work on this project together, Author Lee.

194
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:59,090
I'm sorry.

195
00:13:04,670 --> 00:13:07,020
[You have a new comment]

196
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:11,140
[My News]
[Gameboy]

197
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:13,100
This episode was very fun too.

198
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:17,540
I hope the main character, Ian, won't run away in the next episode.

199
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:20,050
Of course, this is my personal opinion.

200
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:26,890
I don't know who you are, but thank you for always rooting for me.

201
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:30,200
I'll try not to run away this time.

202
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:37,290
Thanks to this mysterious support, I chose not to run away this time.

203
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,900
Since it could be different this time.

204
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:48,040
When should I start?

205
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:13,640
[Gameboy]

206
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:16,720
How did it take seven years?

207
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:37,110
[Gameboy: Of course, this is my personal opinion.]
[Author Wan: I won't run away this time.]

208
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:39,360
[Gameboy]

209
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:45,590
♫ My heart that was so peaceful starts to feel tingly ♫

210
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:51,270
♫ Because of you, you, you, only you ♫

211
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:53,300
♫ It's always like that ♫

